SIMPLE: opiate
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Opiate
<hw>O"pi*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Opium</er>:
cf. F. <ets>opiat</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Originally, a medicine
of a thicker consistency than sirup, prepared with opium.</def>
<rj><au>Parr.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any medicine that contains opium, and has the
quality of inducing sleep or repose; a narcotic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Anything which induces rest or inaction; that which
quiets uneasiness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They chose atheism as an <qex>opiate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bentley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opiate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Opiate
<hw>O"pi*ate</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Opium</er>.]</ety>
<def>Inducing sleep; somniferous; narcotic; hence, anodyne; causing
rest, dullness, or inaction; <as>as, the <ex>opiate</ex> rod of
Hermes</as>.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opiate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Opiate
<hw>O"pi*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To subject to the
influence of an opiate; to put to sleep.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Fenton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opiated</ent>⟦br⟧
